    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-05-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">
                        <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to"
                            >Tyler</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington, D. C.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-05-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 27, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 27.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    dispatch No. 21, of the 21st ultimo, reporting the arrest of the Rev. Mihran
                    Bagdasarian, a naturalized American citizen, for alleged complicity with the
                    revolutionists in Persia.</p>
                <p>Your action securing Mr. Bagdasarian’s release from custody pending his trial is
                    approved by the Department.</p>
                <p>You will thank the acting British consul-general at Tabriz, through the British
                    diplomatic representative at Teheran, for his friendly intervention in
                    Bagdasarian’s behalf.</p>
                <p>Respectfully, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William R. Day.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
